-- China Bans Imports of Meat From Seaboard Pork Plant in Oklahoma, USDA Says
-- Whitney McFerron
-- 2010-08-06T12:55:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/china-bans-imports-of-meat-from-seaboard-pork-plant-in-oklahoma-usda-says.html

          
          
             China, the world’s largest pork
consumer, has banned meat from a Seaboard Corp. plant in Guymon,
Oklahoma, the U.S. Department of Agriculture’s Food Safety and
Inspection Service said on its  website . Meat packed as of June
21 is not eligible for export, the USDA said. The  plant  produces
pork, according to the company’s website.  
